<br>
A. SCARAB is the Society for Cooperative Allied Raids on Antonius Bayle. We are a forum for the organisation of open or inter-guild raids on the Antonius Bayle server in the game Everquest.<br>
<br>
<br>
Q. Who should use SCARAB?<br>
<br>
A. Anyone who is interested in organising or attending joint raids or open raids on AB is welcome to use this forum. It is intended as a communication channel between raid leaders and attendees, who are not able to use a guild messageboard for planning such an event due to the cross guild nature of said event.<br>
<br>
In order to maintain a positive experience for all involved we do require you to register as a member of the forums to take part so we can keep tabs on people's raid attendance and behaviour. If you get lots of bad press from your fellow raiders, you have to learn to become more of a team player or you don't get to remain a member, simple as that.<br>
While we have few hard and fast rules for membership, it is expected that SCARAB will be used mainly by those people in the 46+ crowd who are of a level to do planes raids, dragon raids, raids for pieces of their epic, etc but who are not in a sufficiently large guild to attempt such raids without outside help. Perhaps your guild has a wide range of levels, with only a handful of members high enough to attend this sort of raid. We are here to help.<br>
<br>
We do not expect members from the many huge uber guilds to be too interested in this forum - if you are such a person and wish to raid somewhere, your own guild likely has many such raids of its own. Such people are not specifically excluded from the forums, however - it is hoped that some more public spirited raid-guild members may choose to hold or assist with open raids to give others the benefit of their experience.<br>
<br>
<br>
Q. Who runs SCARAB?<br>
<br>
A. SCARAB is intended as a cooperative effort. It was founded by Elidar Ravenwing, guild leader of Eldritch Circle, in an effort to formalise some of the loose raid alliances being formed by some of the smaller guilds on AB. However, it is hoped that moderators, with the ability to manage the forums and approve memberships, will be drawn from the leadership of many guilds with sufficient presence on these boards.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Q. AB has no calendar and everywhere is FCFS - what's the point in all this?<br>
<br>
A. SCARAB is a forum for the organisation of raids, not a booking calendar. Posting a raid plan and intent to raid somewhere on these forums does not guarantee that a particular raid venue will be available - first in force still applies. Its just that this way, one of the forces turning up to raid somewhere may be a cross-guild joint raiding force rather than an uberguild. If a SCARAB raid force turns up for a raid to find another raid in progress by a large guild or other raiding force, members are expected to respect the current First in Force rules on AB and postpone or move their raid as appropriate.<br>
<br>
Indeed, since this forum is restricted to members, you are advised to copy all announcements of intended raids to the events forum of the AB Community Centre to inform the larger AB community of your plans. <br>
